                {
                    "file": "meta-phosphor/recipes-phosphor/initrdscripts/phosphor-mmc-init/mmc-init.sh",
                    "line": 112,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Patrick Williams",
                        "email": "patrick@stwcx.xyz",
                        "username": "williamspatrick"
                    },
                    "message": "Can you glance at phosphor-static-norootfs-init/init and let me know if there is any change I need to make there?  I would have thought the kernel would have honored the init parameter directly so maybe this change is only needed when you're also doing a chroot?"
                },
                {
                    "file": "meta-phosphor/recipes-phosphor/initrdscripts/phosphor-mmc-init/mmc-init.sh",
                    "line": 112,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Andrew Jeffery",
                        "email": "andrew@aj.id.au",
                        "username": "amboar"
                    },
                    "message": "To affect the binary used for PID 1 in an initrd environment you need to specify `rdinit=` on the kernel command line:\n\nhttps://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/torvalds/linux.git/tree/Documentation/admin-guide/kernel-parameters.txt?h=v6.3#n5226\n\nFrom there the initrd needs to do the things to invoke the correct `init` if you're going to pivot into the \"true root\". So if you've got no true root it should be enough to specify `rdinit` instead?"
                }
            ],
